Various aspects and embodiments of the present invention are defined by the following numbered clauses:
1. A process for preparing a Mn4+ doped phosphor of formula I, ââââââââ Ax [MFy]:Mn+4âââââI the process comprising combining an A+ cation, an anion of formula MFy, and a Mnn+ source comprising a fluoromanganese compound in an acidic solution;
precipitating a Mnn+ containing phosphor precursor from the acidic solution; and
contacting the Mnn+ containing phosphor precursor with a fluorine-containing oxidizing agent in gaseous form, at an elevated temperature, to form the Mn4+ doped phosphor;
wherein
A is Li, Na, K, Rb, Cs, or a combination thereof;
M is Si, Ge, Sn, Ti, Zr, Al, Ga, In, Sc, Hf, Y, La, Nb, Ta, Bi, Gd, or a combination thereof;
x is the absolute value of the charge of the [MFy] ion;
y is 5, 6 or 7; and
n is 2 or 3.
2. A process according to clause 1, additionally comprising combining a fluoride or bifluoride anion, or a combination thereof, with the A+ cation, the anion of formula MFy, and the Mnn+ source.
3. A process according to any preceding clause, wherein the Mn4+ doped phosphor is K2SiF6:Mn4+.
4. A process according to any preceding clause, wherein the anion of formula [MFy] is SiF6.
5. A process according to any preceding clause, wherein the A+ cation is derived from KF, KHF2, or a combination thereof.
6. A process according to any preceding clause, wherein the Mnn+ source is selected from K2MnF5Â·H2O, KMnF4, K2MnF4, KMnF3, MnF2, MnF3, and combinations thereof.
7. A process according to any preceding clause, wherein the Mnn+ source is K2MnF5Â·H2O.
8. A process according to any preceding clause, wherein the acidic solution is aqueous fluorosilicic acid.
9. A process according to any preceding clause, wherein the fluorine-containing oxidizing agent is F2.
10. A process according to any preceding clause, wherein the step of contacting the Mnn+ containing phosphor precursor with the fluorine-containing oxidizing agent additionally comprises contacting the Mnn+ containing phosphor precursor with the fluorine-containing oxidizing agent and compound of formula AX, where X is F, Cl, Br, I, HF2,or a combination thereof.
11. A process according to any preceding clause, comprising
combining a solution comprising fluorosilicic acid and the Mnn+ source with a potassium fluoride compound selected from KF, KHF2, and combinations thereof;
precipitating a Mnn+ containing phosphor precursor; and
exposing the Mnn+ containing phosphor precursor to an atmosphere comprising at least 20% fluorine gas at an elevated temperature, to form the Mn4+ doped phosphor;
wherein the Mnn+ source comprises a potassium fluoromanganese compound selected from K2MnF5Â·H2O, KMnF4, MnF3, and combinations thereof.
